{"key":"post-5134079","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>5134079</id>\n<content>Most likely it would work well, but unless you don't heat your house in the winter, jars will colonize just fine on a bookshelf in your bedroom at normal room temperature.  I haven't used an incubator of any type in years.  You hear far more war stories about getting too warm and ruining the mycelium, than you do success stories because the jar colonized a day or two earlier.  I recommend room temperature.  If you're comfortable in the room wearing a t-shirt, so will your jars.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>5134136</next>\n<prev>5134078</prev>\n<first>5134058</first>\n<last>5144927</last>\n<when>1136287910</when>\n<utime>01/03/06 01:31 PM</utime>\n</post>"}